<figureCitation id="71B52A0AFFE2FF83DB4DFD76F926460F" box="[1624,1790,760,797]" captionStart="FIGURE 69" captionStartId="37.[840,931,2673,2703]" captionTargetBox="[527,1888,1841,2662]" captionText="FIGURE 69.—Approximate range of the gruti group." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828584" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828584/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">Figure 69</figureCitation>
).—I have seen 23 specimens from the following locality:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E931368FFFE2FF83D9C6FCE4F7EB469A" blockId="13.[1233,2101,482,945]" box="[1235,2099,874,904]" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">
CENTRAL 
<emphasis id="DBFAEA9DFFE2FF83D86FFCE4F9CE469A" box="[1402,1558,874,904]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="10">AMERICA</emphasis>
: PANAMA: Canal Zone, Barro Colorado
</paragraph>
